<title>SRI LANKA: Sri Lanka's Dankotuwa Porcelain up 3.6 pct.</title>
<headline>Sri Lanka's Dankotuwa Porcelain up 3.6 pct.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-01-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares of Sri Lanka's Dankotuwa Porcelain Ltd rose 1.0 rupee, or 3.57 percent, to 29, on what brokers said was general optimism about manufacturing stocks.</p>
<p>&quot;The rise in the price is all part of the general optimism felt about manufacturing stocks,&quot; a broker said.</p>
<p>Manufacturing stocks, which suffered a severe setback in 1996 due to power cuts, are expected to perform well in 1997.</p>
<p>Dankotuwa Porcelain manufactures upmarket tableware, mainly for export to the United States and Japan.</p>
<p>-- Colombo newsroom (941) 434319</p>
